2. 🧩 System Architecture

Input Layer (Intent + Context)

{
  "intent": "luxury midnight blue",
  "environment": {
    "lighting": "warm indoor",
    "brightness": 300,
    "time": "evening"
  },
  "surface": "matte fabric",
  "device": "iPhone OLED",
  "observer": {
    "vision_profile": "standard",
    "age": 32
  }
}


⸻

Processing Core (The Engine)

A. Perception Model
	•	Converts raw color → perceived color space
	•	Accounts for:
	•	Human vision (cones, contrast, adaptation)
	•	Simultaneous contrast effects
	•	Light temperature shifts

B. Environment Mapper
	•	Adjusts for:
	•	Lighting (Kelvin shift)
	•	Material reflectance
	•	Display calibration

C. Translation Engine
	•	Outputs:
	•	HEX / RGB (screens)
	•	CMYK / spot (print)
	•	Material recipes (paint, dye, etc.)

⸻

Output Layer (Multi-Substrate Consistency)

{
  "perceived_color_id": "CF-9X2A-LUX-MIDNIGHT",
  "outputs": {
    "screen": "#0A0F2C",
    "print": {
      "cmyk": [100, 85, 30, 60],
      "spot_mix": "custom"
    },
    "fabric": {
      "dye_profile": "navy_adjusted_warm"
    }
  },
  "confidence": 0.94
}


